                <value><![CDATA[Basics of  Fletching
-------------------------------

Fletching is the art of making the ammunition for Bows and Crossbows.

The more skilled the Fletcher, the more sought after are the products.

A Fletcher works with three basic parts, each of which influences the quality of the product.

Shafts, Arrow heads and Fletches are the three parts.

By combining different versions of each of the three parts, a fletcher will produce ammunition of different qualities and strengths.

Shafts can be produced with short oak staffs and a fletching knife.
